        <update></update>
      </pen>
      <pen interval="1.0" mode="1" display="Muertos. Pacientes, conocen edificio" color="-14835848" legend="true">
        <setup></setup>
        <update></update>
      </pen>
      <pen interval="1.0" mode="1" display="Muertos. Pacientes, no conocen edificio" color="-11221820" legend="true">
        <setup></setup>
        <update></update>
      </pen>
    </plot>
    <slider x="40" step="1" y="105" max="200" width="250" display="num-pacientes" height="50" min="0" direction="Horizontal" default="45.0" variable="num-pacientes"></slider>
    <slider x="40" step="1" y="160" max="200" width="250" display="num-sanos" height="50" min="0" direction="Horizontal" default="55.0" variable="num-sanos"></slider>
    <button x="100" y="285" height="40" disableUntilTicks="false" forever="false" kind="Observer" width="55">setup</button>
  </widgets>
  <info>## WHAT IS IT?

(a general understanding of what the model is trying to show or explain)

## HOW IT WORKS

(what rules the agents use to create the overall behavior of the model)

## HOW TO USE IT

(how to use the model, including a description of each of the items in the Interface tab)

## THINGS TO NOTICE

(suggested things for the user to notice while running the model)

## THINGS TO TRY

(suggested things for the user to try to do (move sliders, switches, etc.) with the model)

## EXTENDING THE MODEL

